    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Death Sentence In the Sniper Case?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter form Tom Hoffman says legal authorities in various jurisdictions vying to try sniping case are cynical opportunists</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Along with every thinking person in this country, it is with contempt that I witness the legal authorities in the various jurisdictions involved in the sniping case so desperately trying to have the blood of the accused on their political résumés (front page, Oct. 29).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Along with every thinking person in this country, it is with contempt that I witness the legal authorities in the various jurisdictions involved in the sniping case so desperately trying to have the blood of the accused on their political résumés (front page, Oct. 29).</p>
        <p>Their American constituencies may or may not put these officials into higher office, but the world will certainly judge them to be the cynical opportunists they are.</p>
        <p>TOM HOFFMAN  Hyattsville, Md., Oct. 29, 2002</p>
      </block>
